text: Daniek Hengeveld (born 17 November 2002) is a Dutch professional cyclist riding with GT Krush Tunap. Hengeveld also represents Netherlands at international track cycling competitions. On the road she won the prologue of the Belgrade GP. Later that day in the afternoon stage she broke a vertebra after a fall. On the track she competed at the 2022 UEC European Track Championships in the individual pursuit event where she finished in sixth place in a new Dutch national record. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch cyclists Category:Sportspeople from South Holland Category:Sportswomen
